# Phase 42.3: Shorts Intelligence & Formats

This plan outlines the fixes required to finalize the user's requests regarding vertical video intelligence, number formatting, and mobile swiping functionality.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Upload Intelligence (Vertical Video Detection)
#### [MODIFY] [Upload Page](file:///C:/GOLive/app/upload/page.tsx)
-   **State Upgrade**: Add `[videoMeta, setVideoMeta]` state to capture `width` and `height` from the [getVideoMetadata](file:///C:/GOLive/app/upload/page.tsx#15-31) utility.
-   **Logic Fix**: Enhance the `isShort` calculation. A video will now be classified as a Short if it meets the criteria: `videoDuration <= 60 && videoMeta.width < videoMeta.height`.

### 2. Shorts User Experience
#### [MODIFY] [Shorts Feed](file:///C:/GOLive/app/shorts/page.tsx)
-   **Swipe Fix**: Apply `touch-none` utility class to the main scroll container. This guarantees native mobile browsers won't hijack the vertical swipe (e.g., Pull-to-Refresh or bouncing), ensuring `touchstart` and `touchend` execute the index transition seamlessly.

### 3. Number Formatting
#### [MODIFY] [Utility Formatters](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/utils.ts)
-   **Rounding**: Apply `Math.floor` to incoming values in [formatViews](file:///C:/GOLive/lib/utils.ts#5-16) before formatting to prevent decimals like `1.5` likes. The user requested strict whole-number representation for base counts.

## Verification Plan
-   Verify that clicking "Like" / Hype on a short doesn't result in fractional likes.
-   Verify that the `is_short` flag is correctly calculated in the upload payload for vertical orientations.
-   Run the `browser_subagent` to test the vertical swipe on a simulated mobile view.
